File pictureFelex Share Senior Reporter ELEVEN people were burnt beyond recognition while 14 others were seriously injured when a Honda CRV vehicle collided with a Nissan Caravan at the 60 kilometre peg along the Centenary-Mvurwi road today.The driver of the Honda CRV vehicle reportedly encroached into the lane of the Nissan Caravan at a curve resulting in the head on collision.Both vehicles caught fire upon colliding.Of the deceased, four were in the Honda CRV while seven were travelling in the Nissan Caravan.The Nissan Caravan had 21 passengers on board.Police spokesperson Senior Assistant Commissioner Charity Charamba confirmed the accident.Details to follow .